Package ccre.log

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    LoggingTarget
    A target that can receive logging messages.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BootLogger
    A logging tool that holds the first twenty log messages so that they can be viewed over the network.
    FileLogger
    A logging tool that stores logging message in a file on the current computer or robot.
    Logger
    A class containing easy global methods for logging, as well as holding the default logger field.
    LogLevel
    Represents a Logging level.
    NetworkAutologger
    A logging tool that shares all logging between networked cluck systems automatically.
    PrintStreamLogger
    A logging target that will write all messages to the specified PrintStream.
